5) Write a Python program to check whether a year is leap year or not

a=input("enter year")
if(a%4==0) or (a%100==0) or (a%400)==0:
   print( str(a) +" "+ "is a leap year")
else:print(str(a) +" "+ "is not a leap year")
 
o/p:
enter year2015
2015 is not a leap year

enter year 1996
1996 is a leap year


6)
Write a program that accepts a sentence and calculate the number of upper case letters and lower case letters.

Suppose the following input is supplied to the program:

Hello world!

Then, the output should be:

UPPER CASE 1

LOWER CASE 9


a=raw_input("enter string ")
up=0
lo=0
b=list(a)
for i in a:
  if i.isupper():
      up=up+1
  if i.islower():
      lo=lo+1
print("Number of lower characters are: "+" " +str(lo))
print("Number of upper characters are:"+ " "+str(up))

o/p:
enter string radha uNHAK
Number of lower characters are: 6
Number of upper characters are: 4
   


